Premier Foods has found itself at the centre of a potentially damaging cancer scare after using in its products chilli powder contaminated with Sudan 1 -- an illegal red dye used for colouring non-edible items such as gasoline and shoe polish.
Heinz, a goliath international food manufacturer, has issued a national recall of chilli sauces and chilli oils that may contain the red industrial dye, Sudan I, Monday's China Daily reported.
